A court in Meru has released a man on a Sh100 bail for stealing 15 passion fruits worth Sh60.Augustine Mwenda denied the charge and told Meru Principal Magistrate Monica Maroro that he was given the fruits by Evangeline Kamiri on Saturday in Magundu Village. The owner told me to collect the passion fruits that had fallen down from the tree, Mr Mwenda said.The case will be heard on October 17. email print email print Advocate Wafula Chebukati replaces Issack Hassan as IEBC chairman. Job boycott should be suspended to allow room for talks this week, judge rules.